<D>__{louise?... the maid?...}
<P>__{(a look to hayes)}
<D>__{but she should have left earlier today...}
<C>__{chance}
<P>__{(smiles at hayes)}
<D>__{i see...}
<C>__{franklin}
<P>__{(a beat)}
<D>__{... you've quite a sense of humor, mr. chance but all kidding aside, may i ask just what you are doing here?}
<C>__{chance}
<D>__{i live here.}
<C>__{franklin}
<D>__{you live here?}
<P>__{(a look to hayes)}
<D>__{... we don't have any record of that.}
<C>__{chance}
<D>__{yes. it's very cold outside today, isn't it, thomas?}
<C>__{franklin}
<P>__{(a beat)}
<D>__{... how long have you been living here?}
<C>__{chance}
<D>__{ever since i can remember, since i was a child.}
<C>__{franklin}
<P>__{(doubting)}
<D>__{since you were a child?}
<C>__{chance}
<D>__{yes, thomas. i have always been here. i have always worked in the garden.}
<C>__{hayes}
<D>__{... then you really are a gardener?}
<C>__{chance}
<D>__{yes.}
<C>__{hayes}
<D>__{your appearance doesn't suggest that at all, mr. chance.}
<C>__{chance}
<D>__{oh. thank you.}
<C>__{franklin}
<D>__{do you have any proof of your employment, mr. chance any checks from the deceased, any contracts or documents?}
<C>__{chance}
<D>__{no.}
<C>__{franklin}
<D>__{how were you compensated for these duties you say you performed?}
